## Demo Scenarios

### Scenario 1: YouTube Comparison
**Video A**: "Python Tutorial" - 100K views, 5K likes, 2K comments → 7% engagement
**Video B**: "Python Course" - 50K views, 2K likes, 500 comments → 5% engagement

**Q**: "Why does A have better engagement?"
**A**: "Video A's hook in the first 5 seconds is more compelling. [Chunk A-3]. The pacing maintains viewer retention. [Chunk A-7]. Video B has longer intro which loses viewers. [Chunk B-2]"

### Scenario 2: Cross-platform Analysis
**Video A**: YouTube tutorial (high reach)
**Video B**: Instagram Reel (high engagement)

**Q**: "What can the YouTube creator learn from the Reel creator?"
**A**: "The Reel uses aggressive cuts at 0.5-1s intervals [B-1], maintaining attention. The YouTube video has 5s+ static shots [A-4], which loses viewers. Recommendation: Use B's editing style with A's detailed explanations."

